<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-16T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-16T12:00:00-05:00" n="1168" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1168">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/868.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                    Ambassador</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-16T12:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 16, 1912—12
                                noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>See Department’s September 15, 11 p.m. Date note September 15 and
                            officially present it to the Minister for Foreign Affairs in accordance
                            with the Department’s instruction No. 966, of September 5. The
                            Department regards it as of the greatest importance that this note
                            should be presented at the earliest possible moment and be a matter of
                            record prior to the occurrence of any possible <hi rend="italic">coup
                                d’état</hi>, of which several rumors have recently reached the
                            Department.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>